<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
<A NAME="eolPage51"></A>
<A NAME="STC1231201510-K_HTM_S79D754D15A375513A8F8C325AC0BBF22">
</A>
<BR>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	At
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, Level 1 financial instruments consist of equity securities. Level 2 financial instruments consist of municipal, governmental, and corporate bonds, both U.S. and foreign. In accordance with the Company&#8217;s policies and guidelines which incorporate relevant statutory requirements, the Company&#8217;s third-party registered investment manager invests only in securities rated as investment grade or higher by the major rating services, where observable valuation inputs are significant. All municipal, foreign, and U.S. Treasury bonds are valued using a third-party pricing service, and the corporate bonds are valued using the market approach, which includes three to ten inputs from relevant market sources, including Financial Industry Regulatory Authority&#8217;s (FINRA) Trade Reporting and Compliance Engine (TRACE) and independent broker/dealer quotes, bids and offerings, as well as other relevant market data, such as securities with similar characteristics (i.e. sector, rating, maturity, etc.). Broker/dealer quotes, bids and offerings mentioned above are gathered (typically three to ten) and a consensus risk premium spread (credit spread) over risk-free Treasury yields is developed from the inputs obtained, which is then used to calculate the resulting fair value.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	There were no transfers of investments between Level 1 and Level 2 during the three years ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>

	As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015

	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:4PX;PADDING-TOP:4PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The carrying amount of certain cost-basis investments exceeded their fair value and impairment charges of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$0.6 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;were recorded in Investment and other (losses) gains &#8211; net for the years ended December 31,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	, respectively. The valuations were based on the values of the underlying assets of the investee.

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	At
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and 2014, net deferred tax assets (liabilities) for U.S. federal tax paying components totaled approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$3.8 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$(12.0) million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively, and net deferred tax liabilities for foreign tax paying components totaled approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$0.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$0.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively. The net decrease to the valuation allowance during 2015 and 2014 was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$0.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$4.4 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	During 2008, the Company recorded a valuation allowance against U.S. deferred tax assets, net of definite-lived deferred tax liabilities, for which realization could not be assured based on a more-likely-than-not standard. The Company retained that valuation allowance for all subsequent periods through December&#160;31, 2011 principally due to the Company&#8217;s cumulative three-year operating loss history as of the end of each period. The Company routinely evaluates the extent to which the valuation allowance may be reversed. During 2013, the Company utilized the remaining portion of its U.S. federal NOL carryforwards and released a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$6.6 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;valuation allowance on foreign tax credit carry forwards that it believed will, on a more-likely-than-not-basis, be utilized prior to expiration. During 2014, the Company released the remaining
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$5.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;valuation allowance on foreign tax credit carryforwards. The Company believes it is more-likely-than-not it will be able to utilize its net deferred tax assets.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company&#8217;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$20.2 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;of foreign tax credit carryforwards at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;expire in varying amounts from 2020 through
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2023
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. The Company's
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$6.4 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;of deferred tax assets relating to NOL carryforwards include certain state amounts expiring in varying amounts from 2019 through 2035 and foreign amounts expiring in varying amounts from 2020 through 2022 or having unlimited carryforward periods. The future utilization of all NOL and foreign tax credit carryforwards is subject to various limitations. The remaining valuation allowance at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;relates principally to certain state and foreign NOL carryforwards.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company&#8217;s income tax returns are routinely subject to examinations by U.S. federal, foreign, and state and local tax authorities. During 2014, the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) completed its examination of calendar years 2005 through 2008 and the Company received anticipated refunds from previously-filed carryback claims in the amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$2.8 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. Also during 2014, the IRS completed its examination of the calendar year 2012 U.S. federal tax return without any IRS-initiated adjustments. The Company also is involved in routine examinations by state and local tax jurisdictions for calendar years 2008 through 2014. The Company expects no material adjustments from any tax return examinations.
</FONT>
</DIV>

<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BOTTOM;BORDER-BOTTOM:3PX DOUBLE #000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#CCEEFF;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;">

	217,722
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BOTTOM;BORDER-BOTTOM:3PX DOUBLE #000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#CCEEFF;">

<BR>
</FONT>

</TABLE>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The purchase adjustments recorded for 2015 were related to the remeasurement of assumed liabilities related to certain acquisitions from 2014.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company evaluates goodwill for impairment annually based on information as of June 30 of the current year or more frequently if circumstances suggest that impairment may exist. During 2015 and 2014, management utilized the qualitative assessment for the title reporting units to determine whether it is more likely than not that the fair value of each reporting unit is less than its carrying amount, including goodwill. Based on that analysis, management concluded that the goodwill related to the reporting units within the title segment was not impaired.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In 2014, the Company performed a quantitative assessment of the mortgage services segment's goodwill and determined that there was no impairment of goodwill. In July 2015, the Company made the decision to exit the delinquent loan servicing activities included in the mortgage services segment. The Company based its decision to exit these operations on rapidly falling revenues, declining profit margins and the likelihood that future market demand for the related services would continue to diminish. This resulted in a review of the recoverability of goodwill related to the mortgage services segment. Accordingly, the Company performed the quantitative assessment for mortgage services' goodwill. Based on its impairment analysis using the two-step method, the Company recorded a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$35.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;impairment of mortgage services' goodwill for 2015. This impairment is presented as Impairment of goodwill in the 2015 consolidated statement of operations and comprehensive (loss) income.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company also performed an impairment analysis of other intangible assets within the mortgage services segment for 2015. Based on the Company's impairment review using the discounted cash flow technique to estimate fair value, the Company recorded an impairment of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$0.9 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;on an intangible asset. During 2014, the Company recorded an impairment of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;relating to an intangible asset of a separate business under the mortgage services segment. Further, the Company recognized in 2015 a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$0.9 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;impairment relating to an intangible asset under the title segment that will not be recoverable in future periods. These impairment losses are included in Investment and other (losses) gains - net in the consolidated statements of operations and comprehensive (loss) income.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The gross carrying amount and accumulated amortization and impairment of other intangibles was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$43.6 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$25.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively, at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$43.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, the Company had available a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$125.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;unsecured line of credit commitment (the Credit Agreement), which expires October 2019, under which borrowings of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$98.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;were outstanding. The unsecured line of credit can be used for general corporate purposes, including acquisitions. Borrowings, at the Company's election, bear interest at either (a) an Alternate Base Rate plus the Applicable Rate (ABR Borrowing) or (b) LIBOR plus the Applicable Rate (Eurodollar Borrowing). The Applicable Rate ranges from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	0.50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1.00%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;per annum for ABR Borrowings and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1.50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2.00%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;per annum for Eurodollar Borrowings based on the Company's consolidated Leverage Ratio.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Also, under the terms of the Credit Agreement, the Company may at any time, subject to certain conditions, request an increase in the amount of the line of credit up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$50.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. The Credit Agreement contains customary affirmative and negative covenants. The Credit Agreement also contains certain consolidated financial covenants providing that (a) the ratio of EBITDA (as defined in the Credit Agreement) to fixed charges (as defined in the agreement) not be below
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1.25
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;to 1.00 on a trailing four-quarter basis (Fixed Charge Ratio); (b) the ratio of total Indebtedness to EBITDA for the prior four consecutive quarters must not be greater than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2.25
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;to 1.00 (Leverage Ratio); and (c) Capital Expenditures in the aggregate for the Company consolidated in any calendar year may not exceed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$20.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, with certain allowances for carryover of unused amounts. The Company was in compliance with all covenants as of&#160;December&#160;31, 2015 and 2014.
</FONT>
</DIV>

The First Amendment amends the Credit Agreement, effective as of December 31, 2015, to, among other things, (i) establish an exception to the limitation on restricted payments under the Credit Agreement for the cash payment of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$12.0 million

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$50.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, as announced in November 2015, (iii) increase the general permitted restricted payments (dividends) basket in Section 6.07 of the Credit Agreement from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$25.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;annually,&#160;(iv) provide for an exclusion from the calculation of EBITDA of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;impairment charge recorded in the quarter ended September 30, 2015, and (v) increase the amount of capital expenditures permitted in any calendar year from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The loss ratio on the total provision recorded for the year ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;reflected an ultimate loss rate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	3.6%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;for policies issued in the current year and a net increase in the loss reserve estimates for prior policy years of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$38.2 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. The increase in the loss reserve estimate for prior policy years included
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$6.2 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;related to adverse loss development due to continued elevated claims payment experience for certain years and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$29.1 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;related to provisions for large title claims. Total provisions for large title claims related to prior policy years were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$31.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$3.1 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$28.8 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2013
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</DIV>

</FONT>

</FONT>

Provisions for prior policy years during 2014 and 2013 included adverse loss development of

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 12
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:6PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Common Stock and Class B Common Stock.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;Holders of Common and Class B Common Stock have the same rights except no cash dividends may be paid on Class B Common Stock. The two classes of stock vote separately when electing directors and on any amendment to the Company&#8217;s certificate of incorporation that affects the two classes unequally.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	A provision of the by-laws requires an affirmative vote of at least two-thirds of the directors to elect officers or to approve any proposal that may come before the directors. This provision cannot be changed without a majority vote of each class of stock.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Holders of Class B Common Stock may, with no cumulative voting rights, elect
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	four
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	nine
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;directors if 1,050,000 or more shares of Class B Common Stock are outstanding;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;directors if between 600,000 and 1,050,000 shares are outstanding; and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	none
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;if less than 600,000 shares of Class B Common Stock are outstanding. Holders of Common Stock, with cumulative voting rights, elect the balance of the nine directors.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<BR>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	F - 22
</FONT>
</DIV>

<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
<A NAME="eolPage58"></A>
<BR>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Class B Common Stock may be converted by its stockholders into Common Stock on a share-for-share basis, although the holders of Class B Common Stock have agreed among themselves not to convert their stock. The agreement may be extended or terminated by them at any time. Such conversion is mandatory on any transfer to a person who is not a lineal descendant (or spouse or trustee of such descendant) of William H. Stewart, founder of Stewart Title Guaranty Company.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On January 26, 2016, the Company entered into an Exchange Agreement with the holders of Class B Common Stock relating to the exchange of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1,050,012
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;Class B Common Stock shares, representing all outstanding Class B Common Stock, for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1,050,012
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;shares of Common Stock plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$12.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in aggregate cash. The Exchange Agreement is subject to several conditions, which include, among others, the approval by the Company's stockholders of the Exchange Agreement and the Company's by-laws during the 2016 annual meeting of stockholders and the approval of the listing of the Common Stock by the New York Stock Exchange.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	At
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>

	2014

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	145,820
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;shares of Common Stock held by a subsidiary of the Company which are included in the Treasury stock reported in the consolidated balance sheets.
</FONT>

<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
<A NAME="eolPage59"></A>
<A NAME="STC1231201510-K_HTM_SB044378E259450C588AB0E181233B7A0">
</A>
<BR>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 14
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:6PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Earnings per share.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;The Company&#8217;s basic (loss) earnings per share attributable to Stewart is calculated by dividing net (loss) income attributable to Stewart by the weighted-average number of shares of Common Stock and Class B Common Stock outstanding during the reporting periods.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	To calculate diluted earnings per share, net income and number of shares are adjusted for the effects of any dilutive shares. Using the if-converted method, net income is adjusted for interest expense, net of any tax effects, applicable to the Convertible Senior Notes, which were fully converted into common stock during October 2014. The number of shares is adjusted by adding the number of dilutive shares, assuming they are issued, during the same reporting period. The treasury stock method is used to calculate the dilutive number of shares related to the Company&#8217;s long term incentive and stock option plans. In periods of loss, dilutive shares are excluded from the calculation of the diluted loss per share and diluted loss per share is computed in the same manner as basic loss per share.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The calculation of the basic and diluted (loss) earnings per share is as follows:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 15
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Reinsurance.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;As is industry practice, the Company cedes risks to other title insurance underwriters and reinsurers on certain transactions. However, the Company remains liable if the reinsurer should fail to meet its obligations. The Company also assumes risks from other underwriters on a transactional basis as well as on certain reinsurance treaties. Payments and recoveries on reinsured losses were insignificant during each of the years ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2013
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. The total amount of premiums for assumed and ceded risks was less than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1.0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;of consolidated title revenues in each of the last three years.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<A NAME="STC1231201510-K_HTM_S38EC18F30B635E1DB9EAC81004F625DD">
</A>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 17
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:6PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Contingent liabilities and commitments.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;The Company routinely holds third-party funds in segregated escrow accounts pending the closing of real estate transactions resulting in a contingent liability to the Company of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1.3 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. In addition, the Company is contingently liable for disbursements of escrow funds held by agencies in those cases where specific insured closing guarantees have been issued.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company owns a qualified intermediary in tax-deferred property exchanges for customers pursuant to Section&#160;1031 of the Internal Revenue Code. The Company holds the proceeds from these transactions until a qualifying exchange can occur. This resulted in a contingent liability to the Company of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1.0 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. As is industry practice, escrow and Section&#160;1031 exchanger fund accounts are not included in the consolidated balance sheets.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In the ordinary course of business, the Company guarantees the third-party indebtedness of certain of its consolidated subsidiaries. As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, the maximum potential future payments on the guarantees are not more than the related notes payable recorded in the consolidated balance sheets (refer to Note 10). The Company also guarantees the indebtedness related to lease obligations of certain of its consolidated subsidiaries. The maximum future obligations arising from these lease-related guarantees are not more than the Company&#8217;s future minimum lease payments (refer to Note 16). As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, the Company also had unused letters of credit aggregating
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$5.6 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;related to workers&#8217; compensation coverage and other insurance. The Company does not expect to make any payments on these guarantees.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<A NAME="STC1231201510-K_HTM_S9785CED90488506CAFBF3C3178ADE461">
</A>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 18
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:6PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Regulatory and legal developments.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;In April 2008, Credit Suisse AG, Cayman Islands Branch (Credit Suisse) asserted a claim under a Stewart Title Guaranty Company (Guaranty) policy of title insurance dated on or about May 19, 2006 based upon the alleged priority of mechanic&#8217;s and materialmen&#8217;s liens on a resort development in the State of Idaho known as Tamarack. Guaranty ultimately undertook the defense of the claim under a reservation of rights. For reasons set forth in Guaranty's complaint, on or about May 18, 2011, Guaranty withdrew its defense of Credit Suisse and filed a declaratory judgment action in the United States District Court for the District of Idaho captioned Stewart Title Guaranty Company v. Credit Suisse AG, Cayman Islands Branch seeking a declaratory judgment and other relief. In the lawsuit Guaranty sought, among other things, a determination that it had no duty to indemnify Credit Suisse and sought to have certain provisions of the title insurance policy rescinded. Credit Suisse counterclaimed for, among other things, bad faith for failure to pay the claim.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On August 29, 2013, the United States District Court for the District of Idaho rendered an opinion on Credit Suisse&#8217;s Motion for Partial Summary Judgment. In its opinion the Court, among other things more fully set forth in said opinion, granted Credit Suisse&#8217;s motion negating certain policy defenses to coverage asserted by Guaranty. The Court also granted Credit Suisse&#8217;s Motion to Amend and permitted the assertion of punitive damages against Guaranty.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<BR>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	F - 25
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
<A NAME="eolPage61"></A>
<BR>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Guaranty&#8217;s Motion to Reconsider the Court&#8217;s August 29, 2013 ruling was denied. Guaranty&#8217;s Motion for Summary Judgment based on Credit Suisse&#8217;s lack of standing to pursue its counter claims, and other grounds was denied on February 26, 2015. A jury trial was set to begin on September 3, 2015. That trial date was vacated pending a resolution of the matter through settlement. The matter has now been settled pursuant to a Confidential Settlement Agreement and all amounts have been paid as of December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	* * *
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company is subject to claims and lawsuits arising in the ordinary course of its business, most of which involve disputed policy claims. In some of these lawsuits, the plaintiff seeks exemplary or treble damages in excess of policy limits. The Company does not expect that any of these proceedings will have a material adverse effect on its consolidated financial condition or results of operations. Along with the other major title insurance companies, the Company is party to a number of class action lawsuits concerning the title insurance industry. The Company believes that it has adequate reserves for the various litigation matters and contingencies discussed above and that the likely resolution of these matters will not materially affect its consolidated financial condition or results of operations.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company is subject to administrative actions and litigation relating to the basis on which premium taxes are paid in certain states. Additionally, the Company has received various other inquiries from governmental regulators concerning practices in the insurance industry. Many of these practices do not concern title insurance. The Company believes that it has adequately reserved for these matters and does not anticipate that the outcome of these inquiries will materially affect its consolidated financial condition or results of operations.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company is subject to various other administrative actions and inquiries into its business conduct in certain of the states in which it operates. While the Company cannot predict the outcome of the various regulatory and administrative matters, it believes that it has adequately reserved for these matters and does not anticipate that the outcome of any of these matters will materially affect its consolidated financial condition or results of operations.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<A NAME="STC1231201510-K_HTM_SB4132232768553C89EC8D6F14C267A51">
</A>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 19
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:6PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Segment information.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;The Company&#8217;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;reportable operating segments are title insurance and related services (title), mortgage services and corporate. The title segment provides services needed to transfer the title in a real estate transaction. These services include searching, examining, closing and insuring the condition of the title to the property. The title segment also includes home and personal insurance services and Internal Revenue Code Section&#160;1031 tax-deferred exchanges.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The mortgage services segment includes a diverse group of products and services provided to multiple markets. These services include providing origination and servicing support; default and REO services; post-closing outsourcing; portfolio due diligence; mortgage compliance solutions; servicer oversight to residential mortgage lenders, servicers and investors; technology to support the real estate transaction, and centralized title and valuation services to large lenders. The single largest customer of the mortgage services segment accounted for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	41.1%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	51.4%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	74.5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;of mortgage services revenues in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2013
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The corporate segment consists of the expenses of the parent holding company, certain other corporate overhead expenses, and the costs of its centralized support operations not otherwise allocated to the operating segments. The revenues for the segment are primarily related to investment income.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<BR>
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	F - 26
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Selected statement of operations information related to these segments is as follows:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">

</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BOTTOM;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">

	&#160;

</A>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:24PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 20
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Acquisitions.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;During 2014, the Company completed acquisitions of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;companies that provide collateral valuation, settlement services, title and closing services, and quality control and due diligence services for an aggregate purchase price of $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	40.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, net of liabilities assumed. The acquisitions were primarily funded by borrowings on the Company&#8217;s unsecured line of credit. The Company has recorded fair value estimates for the assets acquired, liabilities assumed and estimated goodwill of $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	20.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, based on the completion of the Company&#8217;s purchase price allocation as of December 31, 2014. During 2015, the Company recorded purchase adjustments of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$5.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;related to the remeasurement of assumed liabilities related to these acquisitions.
</FONT>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</DIV>
<A NAME="STC1231201510-K_HTM_S7952836FC2794E30887A10C9093B544D">
</A>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 22
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exit activities.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	During the third quarter 2015, management approved the exit plan for the delinquent loan servicing activities included in the mortgage services segment. The decision was based on continued pricing pressures on existing contracts and decreased demand for these services. The Company is operating the delinquent loan servicing business on a phased exit schedule and anticipates the completion of its exit no later than the end of first quarter 2016. The Company has estimated the total charge to be incurred related to exiting these operations to be between
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$5.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$7.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. These costs include lease termination costs, additional severance expenses and accelerated amortization expense. For the year ended December 31, 2015, the Company recorded
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$3.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;million of costs, comprised of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;million of employee termination benefits (of which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$0.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;was paid during 2015),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;of early lease termination costs accrued and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;million of accelerated depreciation of assets. These amounts are included within the Employee costs, Investments and other (losses) gains - net and Depreciation and amortization lines, respectively, in the consolidated statement of operations and comprehensive (loss) income.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>

<EFX_CERTIFICATION>
<A NAME="FIS_CERTIFICATION"></A>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:24PX;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CERTIFICATION
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Pursuant to Section&#160;302 of the&#160;Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	I, Matthew W. Morris, certify that:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:6PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1. I have reviewed this annual report on Form 10-K of Stewart Information Services Corporation (registrant);
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2. Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	3. Based on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	4. The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e)) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f)) for the registrant and have:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:4.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:4.5PT;">
	&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<DIV STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PX;TEXT-INDENT:0PX;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;PADDING-TOP:10PX;">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;WIDTH:99.78632478632478%;BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;">

<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared;
</FONT>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;WIDTH:100%;BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;">

</DIV>

<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	designed such internal control over financial reporting, or caused such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision, to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles;
</FONT>

<A NAME="FIS_CERTIFICATION_2"></A>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:24PX;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CERTIFICATION
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Pursuant to Section&#160;302 of the&#160;Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	I, J. Allen Berryman, certify that:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:6PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1. I have reviewed this annual report on Form 10-K of Stewart Information Services Corporation (registrant);
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:6PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2. Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	3. Based on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	4. The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e)) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f)) for the registrant and have:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:4.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:4.5PT;">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:4.5PT;">
	&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<DIV STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PX;TEXT-INDENT:0PX;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;PADDING-TOP:10PX;">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;WIDTH:100%;BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;">

	(d)

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	disclosed in this report any change in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant&#8217;s most recent fiscal quarter (the registrant&#8217;s fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an annual report) that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting; and
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>

	5. The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer and I have disclosed, based on our most recent evaluation of internal control over financial reporting, to the registrant&#8217;s auditors and the audit committee of the registrant&#8217;s board of directors (or persons performing the equivalent functions):

	PURSUANT TO SECTION 906 OF THE SARBANES-OXLEY ACT OF 2002

</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In connection with the Annual Report of Stewart Information Services Corporation (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) on Form 10-K for the period ended December&#160;31, 2015, as filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission on the date hereof (the &#8220;Report&#8221;), I, J. Allen Berryman, Chief Financial Officer, Secretary, Treasurer and Principal Financial Officer of the Company, certify, pursuant to 18 U.S.C. &#167;1350, as adopted pursuant to Section&#160;906 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002, that to my knowledge:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	(1) the Report fully complies with the requirements of Section&#160;13(a) or 15(d) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934; and
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TAHOMA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	(2) the information contained in&#160;the Report fairly presents, in all material respects, the financial condition and results of operations of the&#160;Company.
</FONT>
